	abstract = {The story of AI in education is not only about how technology transforms classrooms, curricula, and access; it is also about how people themselves must adapt to use these tools wisely. Since the earliest days of the personal computer, society has recognized the importance of equipping people with the ability to interact with technology. The proliferation of digital skills has been enabled by the simplification of the use of digital technologies. Over the years, operating systems and applications have become dramatically more user-friendly. Graphical interfaces replaced command lines. Plug-and-play hardware eliminated the need for manual configuration. In education, the key is to treat the challenges as a training ground. International organizations, governments, and private companies all have roles to play. Initiatives to train teachers, provide community learning hubs, and build culturally relevant AI tools can help address widening gaps in AI education. Copyright © 2026 by John Wiley & Sons, Inc. All rights reserved, including rights for text anddata mining and training of artificial intelligence technologies or similar technologies.},
